A good rule of thumb to go by with propagation (and plants in general,) is that they’ll tell you how they feel. 

If the plant needs water, it will usually appear dry, off-color, or withered.

If the plant needs more sun, it may droop, pale in color, reach towards the sun, etc.

In this case, I can tell you that your rubber plant is happy! The leaves are shiny and healthy. And the fact that your plant produced a leaf (and one on the way, from the looks of it) tell me that your plant is thriving!
